The paper deals with an algorithmic problem related to graphs and metric spaces, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of path graphs and the focus on optimizing the diameter of the resulting graph suggest that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem of adding a new edge to a graph also suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of algorithmic techniques and observations to improve the running time suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
